social_posts.post_text: This week we celebrated our 20th wedding anniversary with a trip to the Cloisters. Will knows the way to my heart is old marble, sarcophagi and gardens. Obsessed with the multi colored marble columns and the wavy stone carving. That must have been quite the accomplishment hand carving that kind of movement in uniform around the 1100s. The smell of jasmine filled the hall with potted plants. I also was able to finally see the unicorn tapestries in person, which I loved as a child. I didn’t recall them being as violent as they are, I was laser focused on the unicorn as a kid. This weekend, sanding and priming two rooms on the third floor. #historicplaces #architecture
Very satisfying priming day. The first room on the third floor gets fresh coat on the walls. #verysatisfying #renovation #oldhomerenovations #historichomes

The authenticity of zero to minimal changes to original Waterhouse and Thomas Strahan archives shines today in our @thomas.strahan collection. Old house maven Susan of @houseofbrinson will be customizing Starflower TS 14012 for her #reproductionremix! As you can see from the original document - there’s even one of our archives in the @cooperhewitt ! - to the version we sold over two centuries, to one done today for the @appletv program @dickinson - hasn’t changed a bit except for standard colors that appeal to 2023 tastes. Pro tip: this pattern is wonderful for coastal design!
